<div id="review_869684957" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/869684957" />
    <a title="Philippe Malzieu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28168594-philippe-malzieu"><img alt="Philippe Malzieu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1443697362p2/28168594.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/869684957?book_show_action=true">Mar 02, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Philippe Malzieu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Philippe Malzieu" href="/user/show/28168594-philippe-malzieu">Philippe Malzieu</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer869684957" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15151497647461625819">300,000 specimens for that. To my knowledge no religion exert in France a sufficient magister to endanger the Republic. Such a pulling can only leave perplexed.<br/>In a surprising way, Onfray is undoubtedly the philosopher more listened in Ftance. <br/>He had published a &quot;contre-histoire&quot; of the philosophy which, even if I do not share his opinion is relevant. He&apos;s gauchist, he has some style and he writes well. I think there is the principals reasons of his success. The troubles start when he is interes</span>
  <span id="freeText15151497647461625819" style="display:none">300,000 specimens for that. To my knowledge no religion exert in France a sufficient magister to endanger the Republic. Such a pulling can only leave perplexed.<br />In a surprising way, Onfray is undoubtedly the philosopher more listened in Ftance. <br />He had published a "contre-histoire" of the philosophy which, even if I do not share his opinion is relevant. He's gauchist, he has some style and he writes well. I think there is the principals reasons of his success. The troubles start when he is interested on particular subjects. He loses any rigour then and becomes a true Soviet prosecutor.<br />One of these books takes about psychanalysis. Yes Freud analyzed his daughter, yes Freud was authoritaire. But Onfray disregards any historicity. Charcot used basins of water to treat hysteria. The beginnings or a medical discipline are always erratic. <br />And thus there is this book which is supposed to solve the problem of monotheism. And the things are spoiled.<br />And Onfray mixes all. It is question of a council of the VII° and a book which is discussed there. For Onfray it is here that the position of the Christians with women was defines .Problem. It appears that the council ever took place but the work exists to him well. It was published in the XVII and was condemned by the Pope.<br />All has his indictment, he forgets any rigour. He accumulates the facts, references without any retreat and putting them in their context. <br />We can only to be astonished by this success such this amateurism. As much more than, Comte-Sponville (a réal philosopher) published at the same moment a remarkable book on the same subject without success. Onfray for ideological reasons profits from the kindness of the media.<br />I can draw two conclusions from this books. First is that the religion plays the part of scape goat in a country declining in loss of landmarks. The second is more worrying. It is the reduction of the level of thought and critical sense. This mediocrity of the thought gains ground. The French alive philosophers most known are old and made their career in the USA.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15151497647461625819" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


