<span id="freeTextContainer16206573036988413017">For me, this will be a memorable book. While the author&apos;s angry tone/voice was difficult to read through at times, it ultimately served well to make &quot;the case&quot;. <br/><br/>Most important to me, was that the book was foremost philosophical, and than historical. Similar books I&apos;ve read do well to make their point with tangible evidence, but too few really go into the ethical implications of a [Yahweh/God/Allah]-less, religion-less culture, history and world. <br/><br/> </span>
